questions.text:
Match the placentation types in Column-I with their characteristic features and anatomical examples in Column-II, then select the option representing the correct association as per NCERT nomenclature:

 egin{itemize} 
\item[A.] Marginal 
\item[B.] Parietal 
\item[C.] Free Central 
\item[D.] Basal 
\end{itemize}

 egin{itemize} 
\item[p.] Ovules on central axis, septa absent; e.g., Dianthus 
\item[q.] Placenta at the base of ovary, single ovule; e.g., Marigold 
\item[r.] Placenta forms a ridge along ventral suture; e.g., Pea 
\item[s.] Ovules develop on inner wall, ovary becomes two-chambered due to false septum; e.g., Mustard 
\end{itemize}
